  "text": "In this section we outline a spectral theory of NESS applicable to Bose and Fermi reservoirs. Our approach follows the one developed for the Fermi reservoirs in [CITATION_1] . Fix a state, ω 0 , of the form (2.10) with ω p (A) := Tr(e −βpHp A)/Tr(e −βpHp ). In this and the next section we use the following conditions on the coupling functions and the particle Hamiltonian",
